'From Squeak2.9alpha of 12 June 2000 [latest update: #2688] on 24 September 2000 at 1:16:16 pm'!"Change Set:		LayoutChangedOptDate:			24 September 2000Author:			Dan IngallsSuppresses downward propagation of ownerChanged from pasteUpMorphs (mainly worlds) except from extent:.This prevents *lots* of needless screen recomposition (and hopefully none that is necessary ;-)."!!PasteUpMorph methodsFor: 'layout' stamp: 'di 9/24/2000 11:34'!layoutChanged	"PasteUps do not broadcast ownerChanged down to their submorphs	when responding to (upward) layoutChanged events.  Instead, they	do this only in the case of changing extent (qv)."	fullBounds _ nil.	owner ifNotNil: [owner layoutChanged].	(self valueOfProperty: #SqueakPage) ifNotNil: [		self setProperty: #pageDirty toValue: true].		"I am the morph of a SqueakPage, I have changed and 		need to be written out again"! !!PasteUpMorph methodsFor: 'world state' stamp: 'di 9/24/2000 11:37'!extent: aPoint	"While PasteUps do not broadcast ownerChanged downward in layoutChanged,	they do so here."	super extent: aPoint.	worldState ifNotNil:		[worldState viewBox ifNotNil:			[worldState canvas: nil.			worldState viewBox: bounds]].	submorphs size > 0 ifTrue:		["Let submorphs know about a change above"		submorphs do: [:m | m ownerChanged]].! !